<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="cry-v">cry <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kraɪ/    美 /kraɪ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>哭；哭泣：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The child is <strong>crying for</strong> her mother.
孩子哭着要妈妈。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is no good crying over spilt milk.
覆水难收。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-cry-out">2.★ <strong>[书面用语] 喊叫 (cry out)；大声地说：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>“Look out!” I cried.
我大喊道：“小心！”</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She cried the news all over the neighborhood.
她在街坊邻里大肆宣扬这个消息。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="cry-out">cry out</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(因害怕、震惊、疼痛等) 大声叫喊：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She <strong>cried out in / with</strong> pain when her tooth was pulled out.
她拔牙时痛得大叫。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>“Why are you doing this?”she cried out suddenly.
“你为什么要这么做？”她突然大声喊道。</p></div>

<h3 id="cry-out-for">cry out for</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 急需：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The company is crying out for fresh new talent.
这家公司急需新的人才。</p></div></div>